{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":746,"text":"When I was a child, I always\nwanted to be a superhero."},{"time":3476,"text":"I wanted to save the world\nand make everyone happy."},{"time":6936,"text":"But I knew that I'd need superpowers\nto make my dreams come true."},{"time":10753,"text":"So I used to embark\non these imaginary journeys"},{"time":13000,"text":"to find intergalactic objects\nfrom planet Krypton,"},{"time":16513,"text":"which was a lot of fun,\nbut didn't yield much result."},{"time":20061,"text":"When I grew up and realized"},{"time":21824,"text":"that science fiction was not\na good source for superpowers,"},{"time":25000,"text":"I decided instead to embark\non a journey of real science,"},{"time":28346,"text":"to find a more useful truth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30595,"text":"I started my journey in California,"},{"time":33000,"text":"with a UC Berkeley\n30-year longitudinal study"},{"time":36269,"text":"that examined the photos\nof students in an old yearbook,"},{"time":40000,"text":"and tried to measure their success\nand well-being throughout their life."},{"time":44566,"text":"By measuring the students' smiles,"},{"time":46638,"text":"researchers were able to predict"},{"time":48447,"text":"how fulfilling and long-lasting\na subject's marriage would be,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":52688,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":53774,"text":"how well she would score\non standardized tests of well-being,"},{"time":57719,"text":"and how inspiring she would be to others."},{"time":61219,"text":"In another yearbook, I stumbled\nupon Barry Obama's picture."},{"time":64928,"text":"When I first saw his picture,"},{"time":66427,"text":"I thought that his superpowers\ncame from his super collar."}]},{"cues":[{"time":69610,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":70714,"text":"But now I know it was all in his smile."}]},{"cues":[{"time":73650,"text":"Another aha! moment came from a 2010\nWayne State University research project"},{"time":79030,"text":"that looked into pre-1950s\nbaseball cards of Major League players."},{"time":83776,"text":"The researchers found\nthat the span of a player's smile"},{"time":87307,"text":"could actually predict\nthe span of his life."},{"time":90688,"text":"Players who didn't smile in their pictures"},{"time":93000,"text":"lived an average of only 72.9 years,"},{"time":96000,"text":"where players with beaming smiles"},{"time":98605,"text":"lived an average of almost 80 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":101000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":103415,"text":"The good news is that\nwe're actually born smiling."},{"time":106558,"text":"Using 3D ultrasound technology,"},{"time":108567,"text":"we can now see that developing\nbabies appear to smile,"},{"time":112169,"text":"even in the womb."},{"time":114010,"text":"When they're born,\nbabies continue to smile --"},{"time":117000,"text":"initially, mostly in their sleep."},{"time":119000,"text":"And even blind babies smile"},{"time":121000,"text":"to the sound of the human voice."},{"time":124381,"text":"Smiling is one of the most basic,\nbiologically uniform"},{"time":127000,"text":"expressions of all humans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129461,"text":"In studies conducted in Papua New Guinea,"},{"time":131549,"text":"Paul Ekman, the world's most renowned\nresearcher on facial expressions,"},{"time":135844,"text":"found that even members of the Fore tribe,"},{"time":139000,"text":"who were completely disconnected\nfrom Western culture,"},{"time":142196,"text":"and also known for their\nunusual cannibalism rituals,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":145483,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":146791,"text":"attributed smiles\nto descriptions of situations"},{"time":149458,"text":"the same way you and I would."},{"time":151941,"text":"So from Papua New Guinea"},{"time":153657,"text":"to Hollywood"},{"time":156855,"text":"all the way to modern art in Beijing,"},{"time":160291,"text":"we smile often,"},{"time":161720,"text":"and use smiles to express\njoy and satisfaction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":165640,"text":"How many people here in this room\nsmile more than 20 times per day?"},{"time":169283,"text":"Raise your hand if you do."},{"time":171361,"text":"Oh, wow."},{"time":172902,"text":"Outside of this room,"},{"time":174425,"text":"more than a third of us smile\nmore than 20 times per day,"},{"time":177759,"text":"whereas less than 14 percent of us\nsmile less than five."},{"time":182322,"text":"In fact, those with the most amazing\nsuperpowers are actually children,"},{"time":187969,"text":"who smile as many as 400 times per day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":191831,"text":"Have you ever wondered\nwhy being around children,"},{"time":194215,"text":"who smile so frequently,\nmakes you smile very often?"},{"time":199000,"text":"A recent study\nat Uppsala University in Sweden"},{"time":201911,"text":"found that it's very difficult to frown\nwhen looking at someone who smiles."},{"time":206800,"text":"You ask why?"},{"time":208246,"text":"Because smiling\nis evolutionarily contagious,"},{"time":210730,"text":"and it suppresses the control\nwe usually have on our facial muscles."},{"time":215888,"text":"Mimicking a smile\nand experiencing it physically"},{"time":219340,"text":"helps us understand whether\nour smile is fake or real,"},{"time":223000,"text":"so we can understand\nthe emotional state of the smiler."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227276,"text":"In a recent mimicking study"},{"time":229000,"text":"at the University\nof Clermont-Ferrand in France,"},{"time":232000,"text":"subjects were asked to determine\nwhether a smile was real or fake"},{"time":236000,"text":"while holding a pencil in their mouth\nto repress smiling muscles."},{"time":240809,"text":"Without the pencil,\nsubjects were excellent judges,"},{"time":243737,"text":"but with the pencil in their mouth --"},{"time":245641,"text":"when they could not mimic\nthe smile they saw --"},{"time":248260,"text":"their judgment was impaired."}]},{"cues":[{"time":250190,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":252000,"text":"In addition to theorizing on evolution\nin \"The Origin of Species,\""},{"time":255349,"text":"Charles Darwin also wrote\nthe facial feedback response theory."},{"time":259889,"text":"His theory states that the act of smiling\nitself actually makes us feel better,"},{"time":265418,"text":"rather than smiling being\nmerely a result of feeling good."},{"time":269434,"text":"In his study, Darwin actually cited\na French neurologist, Guillaume Duchenne,"},{"time":274024,"text":"who sent electric jolts to facial muscles\nto induce and stimulate smiles."},{"time":279404,"text":"Please, don't try this at home."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281332,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":283586,"text":"In a related German study,"},{"time":285309,"text":"researchers used fMRI imaging\nto measure brain activity"},{"time":289000,"text":"before and after injecting Botox\nto suppress smiling muscles."},{"time":295000,"text":"The finding supported Darwin's theory,"},{"time":297310,"text":"by showing that facial feedback"},{"time":299207,"text":"modifies the neural processing\nof emotional content in the brain,"},{"time":303000,"text":"in a way that helps us\nfeel better when we smile."},{"time":307680,"text":"Smiling stimulates\nour brain reward mechanism"},{"time":309966,"text":"in a way that even chocolate --"},{"time":311514,"text":"a well-regarded pleasure inducer --"},{"time":314347,"text":"cannot match."}]},{"cues":[{"time":316077,"text":"British researchers found that one smile"},{"time":319267,"text":"can generate the same level\nof brain stimulation"},{"time":322000,"text":"as up to 2,000 bars of chocolate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":327672,"text":"Wait --"},{"time":328855,"text":"The same study found\nthat smiling is as stimulating"},{"time":332686,"text":"as receiving up to 16,000\npounds sterling in cash."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336816,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":337841,"text":"That's like 25 grand a smile."},{"time":339710,"text":"It's not bad."},{"time":341443,"text":"And think about it this way:"},{"time":342912,"text":"25,000 times 400 --"},{"time":345625,"text":"quite a few kids out there feel\nlike Mark Zuckerberg every day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349070,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":350839,"text":"And unlike lots of chocolate,"},{"time":352452,"text":"lots of smiling can actually\nmake you healthier."},{"time":355198,"text":"Smiling can help reduce the level\nof stress-enhancing hormones"},{"time":359069,"text":"like cortisol, adrenaline and dopamine,"},{"time":362274,"text":"increase the level of mood-enhancing\nhormones like endorphins,"},{"time":365992,"text":"and reduce overall blood pressure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":368853,"text":"And if that's not enough,"},{"time":370527,"text":"smiling can actually make you\nlook good in the eyes of others."},{"time":374209,"text":"A recent study at Penn State University\nfound that when you smile,"},{"time":378000,"text":"you don't only appear to be\nmore likable and courteous,"},{"time":381879,"text":"but you actually appear\nto be more competent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":385801,"text":"So whenever you want\nto look great and competent,"},{"time":388199,"text":"reduce your stress\nor improve your marriage,"},{"time":391000,"text":"or feel as if you just had a whole stack\nof high-quality chocolate"},{"time":394912,"text":"without incurring the caloric cost,"},{"time":397000,"text":"or as if you found 25 grand in a pocket\nof an old jacket you hadn't worn for ages,"},{"time":402857,"text":"or whenever you want\nto tap into a superpower"},{"time":406395,"text":"that will help you and everyone around you"},{"time":409381,"text":"live a longer, healthier, happier life,"},{"time":413208,"text":"smile."}]},{"cues":[{"time":414531,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}